    {
      "id": "OG-EX-16",
      "name": "Identity wrapper, terminal error",
      "section": "Transparency (the identity law) / consequence 4",
      "description": "The inner invocation terminates with an error and the conduit has no onError, so the graph invocation terminates with that error: terminal status is preserved, not converted into a successful empty stream. The error detail is the inner terminal error value itself (the value direct invocation would surface), not an error-event wrapper around it.",
